The paper deals with the complexity of solving 3-SAT instances, which is a well-studied problem in theoretical computer science. The paper specifically focuses on a new class of hard 3-SAT instances, which suggests that it could belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of local search algorithms, which could also place it in the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions numerical simulations, which could suggest a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or information theory (cs.IT).
